^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|There is no universal agreement as to how reverses should work. This is the simple approach I use:

1) A reverse forces the auction to end no lower than 2NT. Therefore, if responder's rebid is less than 2N, opener must bid again. If it is higher, opener is not obligated to bid again, except as specified in rule 2.

2) If responder has a medium or max hand, he or she is responsible for making sure their side gets to game. Therefore, with a medium or max hand, responder must do one of the following:
    a) Bid game if possible
    b) Bid 4th suit forcing
    c) Jump in their suit
    d) Make a bid below 2N

If responder fails to do any of those, then opener may pass, and they are not forced to game. Of course, if opener has a max hand, then opener is responsible for making sue their side gets to game when responder makes a non-game forcing bid.|
