AT|
 
A minimum hand is 12-14 points, a medium hand is 15-17 points, and a maximum hand is 18+. Similarly, as responder you can classify your hand as well. A minimum response is 6-8, a medium response is 9-11, and a maximum response is 12+. Hopefully, most of you know that game requires that the combined assets of the two hands are worth at least 25 points. So, say you are responder. If partner opens, and you have a maximum response (12+), you know you have game. If you have a minimum response (6-8), then partner needs a maximum for you to bid game. And if you have a medium response, then partner needs at least a medium opener for you to bid game. I have a table in the tutorial which summarizes what I just said. The point is, you can usually figure out from the first bid or two, what partner's strength is and therefore you can figure out whether or not you have game. That is what you should be doing on every auction. Although I am not focusing on hand evaluation, let me digress a bit. I deduct one point for dubious shortness. So, a singleton King ,Queen, or Jack I subtract 1 point. Same for doubleton Queen or Jack.|
