As I just said, on every auction, you need to think about the strength partner is showing. I will be teaching you today how you can figure that out. Once you figure out partner's strength (minimum, medium, or maximum), you can figure out whether or not you have enough for game. This next part of the lesson is probably very new to many of you. I am going to teach you about the "captain" of the auction. In most every auction, one person is the "captain" and the other person is the "subordinate." The captain is in charge of placing the contract. He or she does this by asking the subordinate questions. The subordinate's job is to answer the questions truthfully.  (some of my partners like to lie in the name of "creativity" :) ). But you should not lie. This is very important.|
