^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Next, let me talk about the captain's tools for controlling the auction. The main tool for responder is the "new suit forcing" principle. If responder bids a new suit, opener may not pass. That is very important. You should never violate it. In fact, some of you are familiar with the "4th suit forcing" convention. That is a very good example of this principle. Most all expert partnerships play 4th suit forcing. What that means is, at responder's second bid, if the 3 other suits have been mentioned and responder bids the one remaining unbid suit--4th suit. First of all, as I already said the 4th suit is forcing for at least one round. But, if you play 4th suit forcing, it is forcing to game. In fact, it may be (and often is), an artificial bid, it is just the way responder controls the auction by establishing a game force. |
