^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So, on the last example, 1@H-P-1@S-P-3@C is a jump shift because opener deliberately bypassed 2@C. Jump shifts show a maximum hand, and establish a game force. Remember, once responder bids something they are showing at least 6 points. So, even if responder has a minimum hand, once opener shows a maximum hand, you are in a game forcing auction. Medium hands are the most difficult to describe. The good news is, many medium hands are opened 1NT (15-17). That is one reason why I (and a majority of experts) advocate opening 1NT even with a 5 card major. If you don't, you often have a problem describing a hand with medium strength.|
