One other thing about reverses. Once opener reverses, they are showing a distributional hand. Opener's first suit is 5+ cards. On my example auction 1@D-1@S-2@H, opener must have 5+ diamonds and 4 hearts. You may think that makes some hands unbiddable but actually it turns out that is not true. Remember with a flat 15-17 you open 1N and with a strong balanced hand 18+, you rebid 2N. So, if you reverse, you have to have an unbalanced hand. Now, its time for some examples.|
