As (responder), you know that opener has a minimum hand. But you know a lot more. And this is where many less experienced people don't realize what they know. You know that opener has at most 3 hearts. With 4 hearts opener would have raised. You also know opener does not have 4 spades. Because opener would bid 1S. These are all "negative inferences." By that I mean, assuming your partner bids correctly, you know almost as much (sometimes more) from what partner did NOT bid as you know from what they bid. You know a few other things as well. Partner has 4 or 5 diamonds and partner almost always has 3 or 4 clubs. Granted, partner could have 3 spades 3 hearts 5 diamonds and 2 clubs. But more often than not, partner tends to have at least a few clubs.|
