What does opener have in strength?
Yes a jump shift, showing a maximum hand and establishing a game force. A jump shift guarantees a maximum and establishes a game force. Remember, you may now not pass below game.

Let's talk about distribution. Opener does not have 4 hearts (did not reverse to 2H). Opener does not have 4 spades (did not bid 4S or splinter). Opener usually has 4 clubs and opener always has at least 5 diamonds.
 
Yes opener could have 3 spades. You can raise 1S to 2S with 3 card support. But you cannot make a jump raise in spades without 4-card support. It is time to summarize the purpose of these examples. The purpose is to get you thinking about what partner has on every auction. Many players only focus on bidding their own cards. They never stop to think about what partner is showing. But bridge is a partnership game and partner is giving you information with every bid. You should take advantage of that information it will often help you make the right choice of bids. And remember the negative inferences (what partner did not bid) as well as the positive inferences. Next, let's look at a few auctions to wrap things up. 

